<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="S" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Seduce" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Seduce,</orth> to mislead, to corrupt, to deprave: <bibl n="shak. luc 639" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 639</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tgv 4.2.97" default="NO" valid="yes">Gent. IV, 2, 97</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lll 1.2.180" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL I, 2, 180</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. aww 3.5.22" default="NO" valid="yes">All's III, 5, 22</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jn 1.254" default="NO" valid="yes">John I, 254</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 2.2.155" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 II, 2, 155</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 3.1.356" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B III, 1, 356</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 4.8.37" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C IV, 8, 37</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 5.1.19" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 1, 19</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 3.7.188" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 III, 7, 188</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 5.6.24" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. V, 6, 24</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jc 1.2.316" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. I, 2, 316</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 1.5.45" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. I, 5, 45</bibl>. cf. <emph>Saint-seducing</emph> in <bibl n="shak. rom 1.1.220" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. I, 1, 220</bibl>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>